[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(15) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "All that pass by.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—The triumphant exultation of the enemies of Zion came to add bitterness to her sorrows. They reminded her of what she had been in the past, and contrasted it with her present desolation.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The perfection of beauty . . .—Like phrases are used of Zion in Psalm 48:2; Psalm 50:2; of Tyre in Ezekiel 27:3. Now that beauty was turned into squalor and desolation.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "The perfection of beauty . . .",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
