  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Strangers and enemies have, for the misfortune of Jerusalem, only expressions of scorn and delight over her loss. \"Those who pass by the way\" are strangers who travel past Jerusalem. To clap the hands together is not here a gesture betokening anger and disinclination (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 24:10",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), but of delight over the injury of others, as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Job 27:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". שׂרק, to hiss, is an expression of scorn; see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 19:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The same is true as regards the shaking of the head; cf. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 22:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 109:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc.: the expression for this, in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Jeremiah 18:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", is הניד בּראשׁ. The exclamation, \"Is this the city which they call 'perfect in beauty'?\" is an expression of scornful astonishment. כּלילת יפי is substantially the same as מכלל יפי, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 50:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the expression is applied to Zion; in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Ezekiel 27:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the same is said of Tyre. That Jeremiah had ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 50:2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
